had I lived here because--

04:58.708 --> 05:02.208
What the fuck?
What?

05:02.208 --> 05:04.625
Okay, you definitely
need to call your super.

05:04.625 --> 05:07.166
This is something
Adam and I always
talked about, you know?

05:07.166 --> 05:09.625
Making a master suite
with our bare hands.

05:09.625 --> 05:12.708
And now it's here
and I have nothing
to do with it.

05:12.708 --> 05:15.500
Okay, Hannah, I understand
this is about your pain

05:15.500 --> 05:17.375
and your devastation, totally,
and I'm gonna get you

05:17.375 --> 05:19.333
a hot cup of tea for that
like in just a mo,

05:19.333 --> 05:21.625
but am I the only one
who doesn't know about this?

05:21.625 --> 05:23.917
We loved each other, Shosh.

05:23.917 --> 05:26.917
We loved each other,
and nothing has changed, okay?

05:26.917 --> 05:28.750
I'm the same person I was
when he loved me.

05:28.750 --> 05:31.000
In fact, I'm an arguably
better person

05:31.000 --> 05:33.041
because I went away
and figured out what I want.

05:33.041 --> 05:35.583
Hannah, we are going
to get through this.

05:35.583 --> 05:37.291
- I want to die.
- No, you don't.

05:37.291 --> 05:40.166
You and me and Jessa
and/or slash Marnie,

05:40.166 --> 05:42.291
we are going to get
through this together.

05:42.291 --> 05:43.625
If they ever show up
or call back.

05:43.625 --> 05:46.875
Also, you have
absolutely lost weight,
and that is a definite.

05:46.875 --> 05:48.458
Yes, two and a half pounds.

05:48.458 --> 05:49.834
Yeah, I know.
That's a lot.

05:49.834 --> 05:52.250
Um, we need to find out
every possible detail

05:52.250 --> 05:54.375
about this rando hussy
immediately.

05:54.375 --> 05:56.250
My laptop's in my bag.

05:56.250 --> 05:57.583
Okay, what's her name again?

05:57.583 --> 05:59.041
Mimi-Rose Howard.

05:59.041 --> 06:00.291
Ew, of course it is.

06:00.291 --> 06:04.917
- ( keyboard clicking )
- Mimi dash Rose space Howard.

06:04.917 --> 06:06.250
I don't know
if I want to do this.

06:06.250 --> 06:08.959
I don't want to be
this woman-googling person.

06:08.959 --> 06:10.083
Okay.

06:13.083 --> 06:17.458
( imitates missile
falling, exploding )

06:19.625 --> 06:22.750
Rhode Island
School of Design,
2007 BFA.

06:22.750 --> 06:27.458
- BFA in what?
- Fine Arts, whatever, with
an emphasis on sculpture.

06:27.458 --> 06:28.625
Um, wait.
Holy shit.

06:28.625 --> 06:31.458
"Mimi-Rose Howard visiting
artist keynote address"?

06:31.458 --> 06:32.750
Wait.
Okay, I wanna see this.

06:32.750 --> 06:34.792
You know what?
I don't think that
we should watch this.

06:34.792 --> 06:37.041
How many of you remember
your first love?

06:37.041 --> 06:39.125
Hands.

06:39.125 --> 06:40.917
Yes, me, too.

06:40.917 --> 06:44.166
When I was nine, I fell in love
for the first time.

06:44.166 --> 06:46.875
The minute I saw Peter,
I knew he would be mine.

06:46.875 --> 06:49.041
Okay, you know what?
We're not watching this.

06:49.041 --> 06:50.959
- It was a bad idea.
- No, I wanna finish it.
I need to finish it.

06:50.959 --> 06:52.208
I just really think
that it's not a good idea.

06:52.208 --> 06:55.750
- I need
to finish it, Shoshanna.
- I think that it-- no!

06:58.166 --> 07:00.041
You know what I think
would be a good idea?

07:00.041 --> 07:01.750
If you and I went
to my lodgings

07:01.750 --> 07:04.291
and I made you
that warm mug of tea
that we were talking about.

07:04.291 --> 07:07.041
- And maybe you took a bath.
- No, thank you.

07:07.041 --> 07:09.083
Bye, Shosh.
Thank you for stopping by.

07:09.083 --> 07:12.542
I just think that this
is really not a safe space--
oh, my God.

07:12.542 --> 07:14.166
Okay, you just boob hit me
with your foot.

07:14.166 --> 07:16.583
- Oh, my God.
- I'm okay.

07:16.583 --> 07:18.667
I just want to be alone.

07:22.458 --> 07:24.583
I think she just needs
some time to digest this.

07:24.583 --> 07:26.667
- Does she need to do it here?
- Uh, it seems like it,

07:26.667 --> 07:29.166
but all will be revealed
in the fullness of time.

07:30.708 --> 07:32.625
I can't believe
you called her first.

07:32.625 --> 07:34.333
I didn't call her first,
she just got here first.

07:34.333 --> 07:36.667
Uh, if I were her,
I'd definitely be
the person

07:36.667 --> 07:38.125
I'd want someone
to call first.

07:38.125 --> 07:39.875
Actually, I called Marnie
before either of you.

07:39.875 --> 07:41.708
- Oh, well, that's nice.
- You're a twat.

07:41.708 --> 07:43.083
You know what,
if you see her,

07:43.083 --> 07:45.542
tell her her services
are no longer needed.

07:47.792 --> 07:50.041
- Hannah?
- Hannah: Who's there?

07:50.041 --> 07:52.458
What is going on?
Why aren't you in Idaho?

07:52.458 --> 07:54.333
What do you care?

07:54.333 --> 07:56.708
What did I do?

07:56.708 --> 08:00.875
I'm sorry, I'm just
really confused right now.

08:00.875 --> 08:03.417
Are you here on furlough?

08:03.417 --> 08:05.667
Adam is seeing someone.

08:05.667 --> 08:08.750
Yeah, right,
Mimi-Rose Howard.

08:08.750 --> 08:11.041
I told you
about her, right?

08:11.041 --> 08:12.333
No.

08:12.333 --> 08:14.917
Jessa, I think
I'd remember if you
told me that my boyfriend

08:14.917 --> 08:16.250
had an entirely
new girlfriend.

08:16.250 --> 08:19.041
- Fair enough.
- I don't understand
what's happening, Jess.

08:19.041 --> 08:22.125
I feel so fucking insane.
How did this even occur?

08:22.125 --> 08:26.583
Well, the heart wants
what the heart wants.

08:26.583 --> 08:29.291
You do know
who you're quoting, right?

08:29.291 --> 08:32.082
I actually am sure
I told you about her.

08:32.082 --> 08:33.417
I distinctly remember.

08:33.417 --> 08:37.917
Jessa, I'm 100% sure
you really didn't.

08:37.917 --> 08:41.707
Okay, so let's put
your mind at ease.

08:41.707 --> 08:42.707
What do you want
to know?

08:42.707 --> 08:45.583
Nothing, everything.
What do I need to know?

08:45.583 --> 08:49.708
( sighs )
Okay, I hadn't seen MRH
in, like, a year or two

08:49.708 --> 08:53.792
and I knew she was single
after the whole Ace thing
blew up

08:53.792 --> 08:56.166
and then I was
talking to Adam
about his predicament...

08:56.166 --> 08:59.125
Oh, my God.
You set them up?

08:59.125 --> 09:01.917
I mean, what's--
I don't understand.
What's the problem?

09:01.917 --> 09:04.458
You said you were
leaving for two years.

09:04.458 --> 09:07.291
Wh-- hold on, what were
we supposed to do,

09:07.291 --> 09:10.291
sit around
flicking our clits
till you got back?

09:10.291 --> 09:13.375
I can't fucking believe this.
I can't believe this.

09:13.375 --> 09:18.125
Oh, my God.
I mean, I don't
want to hurt you.

09:18.125 --> 09:21.875
But the fact is
is that Adam is happy.

09:21.875 --> 09:24.834
And he's really opening up
at our dumb meetings,

09:24.834 --> 09:26.834
which is a good thing.

09:27.959 --> 09:30.792
What is he saying
at the meetings?

09:30.792 --> 09:33.458
Hannah, you know
I can't tell you that.

09:33.458 --> 09:36.625
It's anonymous.
Don't be a child.

09:41.959 --> 09:44.000
Fuck!

09:44.000 --> 09:45.875
