this is about you, okay?

15:13.083 --> 15:18.375
This is about you
and that protohominid
ex-boyfriend of yours.

15:18.375 --> 15:20.000
Okay, yeah, you know what?
Now that you say it,

15:20.000 --> 15:21.458
maybe it is
a little bit about me.

15:21.458 --> 15:23.166
Maybe it is.
Maybe it's about me

15:23.166 --> 15:25.166
and the self-appointed
mandarins and fellow travelers

15:25.166 --> 15:27.208
of Community Board Number Eight.
Quick question for you, Hannah.

15:27.208 --> 15:31.500
Let's say, hypothetically,
there was a very logical,
very expedient solution

15:31.500 --> 15:33.000
to a noise pollution
problem that threatened

15:33.000 --> 15:34.667
the mental health
of the entire community.

15:34.667 --> 15:37.166
Not one individual,
the entire community.

15:37.166 --> 15:39.333
And let's say
the solution to this problem
is so straightforward...

15:39.333 --> 15:43.041
- ( screaming )
- ...so basic, that a failure
to recognize it is--

15:43.041 --> 15:44.583
- Ray.
- What?

15:44.583 --> 15:46.667
- I burned myself.
- Well, put some ice on it,
but hear me out here.

15:46.667 --> 15:49.000
Now let's say
the solution to the problem
is so straightforward,

15:49.000 --> 15:51.625
- so practical,
that a failure to realize it--
- Hannah: Ray, look.

15:51.625 --> 15:54.500
I mean, what we're
essentially talking about--
oh, God.

15:54.500 --> 15:55.834
It's-- that's bad.

15:55.834 --> 15:57.834
We got to, uh--
we need--

15:57.834 --> 16:00.291
does Adam have
a first aid kit
in his workshop?

16:00.291 --> 16:04.333
Or is it all watch springs
and doll heads?

16:04.333 --> 16:07.375
I mean, they could
put a left-turn-only lane.
That would be something.

16:07.375 --> 16:10.333
They could also put just
a left-turn-only signal
on the traffic light.

16:10.333 --> 16:12.208
I mean, either of those
solutions would probably be--

16:12.208 --> 16:14.500
Have you talked
to Marnie lately?

16:14.500 --> 16:15.708
No.

16:15.708 --> 16:18.458
She's with that, uh,
Mumford or Son now, right?

16:18.458 --> 16:19.959
And, no, it doesn't
bother me.

16:19.959 --> 16:22.583
- It doesn't bother you?
- It doesn't bother me.

16:22.583 --> 16:24.166
Okay.

16:25.375 --> 16:26.625
I was her whore, Hannah.

16:26.625 --> 16:28.041
That's what I was.
I was her whore.

16:28.041 --> 16:30.917
- Uh-huh.
- I was her eff buddy, okay?

16:30.917 --> 16:34.125
I'm not the type of person
she's gonna, you know,
end up with.

16:34.125 --> 16:36.000
- I get that.
- Why would you say that?

16:36.000 --> 16:39.625
I'm not exactly
Patrick Dempsey
over here, you know?

16:39.625 --> 16:41.500
I get that,
but I reject the idea

16:41.500 --> 16:43.917
that I'm some sort
of hideous troll

16:43.917 --> 16:45.542
whose photo you wouldn't
want in your wedding album.

16:45.542 --> 16:47.917
- Here, let me see this.
- I don't think you're
a hideous troll.

16:47.917 --> 16:49.291
- Ow.
- No, I'm not.

16:49.291 --> 16:51.792
That's what I'm--
when you say that I'm not,

16:51.792 --> 16:54.750
it sounds like you think
that I am, though,
which is hurtful.

16:54.750 --> 16:57.083
I actually think
it was the age difference.

16:57.083 --> 16:59.333
The age difference?

16:59.333 --> 17:02.083
It wasn't a problem
for Shoshanna, right?

17:02.083 --> 17:04.208
- That's true.
- I'm 34.

17:04.208 --> 17:06.541
Someday,
you guys will be, too,
believe it or not.

17:06.541 --> 17:09.083
What can I say?
It's awful.

17:09.083 --> 17:11.250
All right, so keep that on.
Make sure this part is tight.

17:11.250 --> 17:13.125
- Okay.
- This is what we used
to do in the Boy Scouts

17:13.125 --> 17:15.416
during our wilderness
survival weekends.

17:15.416 --> 17:17.541
Keeps it dry.
Ahem.

17:20.375 --> 17:23.458
Hannah, I'm so sorry
for everything that
you're going through.

17:23.458 --> 17:25.959
- Thank you, Ray.
- I really am.

17:25.959 --> 17:29.083
And I want you
to remember one thing.

17:29.083 --> 17:32.291
You do not deserve this.

17:32.291 --> 17:34.250
Thank you, Ray.

17:34.250 --> 17:37.458
That means a lot to me.

17:37.458 --> 17:40.291
The minute I saw Peter,
I knew he would be mine,

17:40.291 --> 17:42.583
with his flaxen hair
and overalls.

17:42.583 --> 17:44.708
He was like
a Norman Rockwell painting.

17:44.708 --> 17:46.917
And one day on a ride
to an ice cream parlor,

17:46.917 --> 17:49.166
he finally asked me
to hold hands.

17:49.166 --> 17:51.291
( gasps )
I was in heaven.

17:51.291 --> 17:53.875
But that night,
as I tried to read a book,

17:53.875 --> 17:56.333
an activity
that had heretofore
been my favorite,

17:56.333 --> 17:58.208
I found myself
distracted.

17:58.208 --> 17:59.667
Good use of "heretofore."

17:59.667 --> 18:02.375
Mimi-Rose on laptop:
Where's Peter? What is
he thinking about?

18:02.375 --> 18:07.166
My private time,
my time to focus
and learn and grow

18:07.166 --> 18:10.583
was being sliced in half
by my new relationship.

18:10.583 --> 18:12.542
- So, yes, when I was nine...
- ( knock on door )

18:12.542 --> 18:15.834
Marnie:
Hannah, you can come out.
It's just me.

18:15.834 --> 18:18.500
And I brought food.

18:20.291 --> 18:23.625
Hello, Marnie.
Glad to see you're
a person who still exists.

18:23.625 --> 18:26.333
I am so sorry.
Sometimes when Desi
and I are woodshedding,

18:26.333 --> 18:27.834
we go on a cell phone diet.

18:27.834 --> 18:30.792
I'm really sorry.
How are you feeling?

18:30.792 --> 18:33.959
I'm great, okay?
I just need to take
a quick shower.

18:35.208 --> 18:36.333
( door closes )

18:44.959 --> 18:48.708
Mimi-Rose on phone:
So, yes, when I was nine,
I broke up with someone

18:48.708 --> 18:50.125
for hindering
my creativity.

18:50.125 --> 18:53.041
- ( audience laughs )
- And nothing's changed.

18:53.041 --> 18:55.750
Maybe I'm crazy,
but who knows?

18:55.750 --> 18:58.250
Think of all
your ups and downs,

18:58.250 --> 19:01.125
all your
hopes and fears.

19:01.125 --> 19:02.959
How many of them
have been yours

19:02.959 --> 19:06.917
and how many
have been constructs
of romantic discord?

19:09.125 --> 19:10.917
( knock on door )

19:10.917 --> 19:12.375
Hannah?

19:12.375 --> 19:14.166
I'm in the shower!

19:14.166 --> 19:18.542
This is not one of your
more convincing fake showers,
just so you know.

19:18.542 --> 19:20.291
This is not a fake shower!

19:20.291 --> 19:22.500
I'm in the middle
of showering.

19:24.041 --> 19:27.125
Look, I'm really sorry
you and I haven't had

19:27.125 --> 19:29.917
a chance to talk
about this one-on-one.

19:29.917 --> 19:31.083
I really am.

19:31.083 --> 19:33.208
Uh, yeah, that's 'cause
you completely disappeared.

19:33.208 --> 19:35.291
No, I've just--
I've been juggling a lot.

19:35.291 --> 19:37.375
Desi moved in,
which is exciting,

19:37.375 --> 19:39.375
and we've had
a lot of nibbles
from this label,

19:39.375 --> 19:41.875
but, honestly,
I think I've actually
just been avoiding you

19:41.875 --> 19:45.000
because I have no idea
how to say what I need
to say to you.

19:45.000 --> 19:47.917
Great, are you, uh,
breaking up with me, too?

19:47.917 --> 19:50.250
No, Hannah, I love you.

19:50.250 --> 19:52.041
I want you to be happy.

19:53.417 --> 19:56.583
Which is why I think
you need to let Adam go.

19:56.583 --> 19:58.417
No, I don't.

19:58.417 --> 20:00.750
Yeah, you do.

20:00.750 --> 20:02.208
You're the one who left.

20:02.208 --> 20:08.250
And I'm sure he should not
have moved on as quickly,
but he did,

20:08.250 --> 20:10.041
and he's just trying
to be happy.

20:10.041 --> 20:12.333
And if you don't
give him the space

20:12.333 --> 20:15.041
to at least see
where this goes,

20:15.041 --> 20:17.375
he's gonna
hate you forever

20:17.375 --> 20:19.875
and you'll hate
yourself.

20:19.875 --> 20:22.500
Just trust me.

20:22.500 --> 20:24.041
You have to let him go.

20:24.041 --> 20:27.667
Letting go doesn't come
very naturally to me.

20:27.667 --> 20:31.250
I know that,
and it's fucking hard,

20:31.250 --> 20:35.750
but did you really think
you and Adam were gonna
be a forever couple?

20:35.750 --> 20:38.625
I would've liked
the chance to find out.

20:38.625 --> 20:41.792
I think you have
found out.

20:41.792 --> 20:44.959
I think you have
your answer.

20:44.959 --> 20:46.542
( deep breath )

20:46.542 --> 20:50.000
So I guess we're not
like some great, artistic
love story.

20:51.583 --> 20:53.375
Maybe we are.

20:53.375 --> 20:55.375
You and me?

20:58.083 --> 21:00.375
Fine, I'll take it.

21:08.333 --> 21:10.333
Mimi-Rose?

21:11.708 --> 21:14.458
- ( door opens )
- Mi-- hey.

21:14.458 --> 21:17.834
Hey, I was just leaving.

21:17.834 --> 21:20.291
Oh, for good, or...

21:21.166 --> 21:23.166
Yeah, you can
take that, I guess.

21:23.166 --> 21:24.542
You want the other one?
It came with two.

21:24.542 --> 21:27.333
Um, I'll just
be needing the one.
It's my cast.

21:27.333 --> 21:30.083
Ray gave it to me
'cause I burned myself
pretty badly.

21:30.083 --> 21:31.417
Oh, fuck.

21:31.417 --> 21:34.542
You mind
if I check it out?

21:39.291 --> 21:41.333
( winces )

21:41.333 --> 21:43.500
Fuckin' Ray.

21:43.500 --> 21:45.708
Guy fancies himself
some kind of Renaissance man,

21:45.708 --> 21:47.375
but he doesn't know
jack shit about fuck.

21:47.375 --> 21:49.208
- It's really fine.
- No, that's bad.

21:49.208 --> 21:51.708
Go ahead and have a seat.
I'm gonna go grab my gear.

21:54.875 --> 21:56.083
Where's Mimi-Rose?

21:56.083 --> 21:58.542
I don't know.
Probably working late
at her studio.

21:58.542 --> 22:03.875
Wow, she has her own studio?
That's... really cool.

22:06.625 --> 22:09.458
Adam, I'm not proud
of my behavior yesterday.

22:09.458 --> 22:11.875
I would say it was not
my finest hour.

22:14.041 --> 22:15.875
I guess there was
just a part of me

22:15.875 --> 22:18.166
that thought that you would,
you know, wait for me

22:18.166 --> 22:21.000
or at least never meet anyone
who could possibly replace me.

22:21.000 --> 22:22.417
I know we didn't
make any promises,

22:22.417 --> 22:26.542
but that's just
what I thought.

22:26.542 --> 22:29.291
I mean, I had what
at the time seemed like

22:29.291 --> 22:30.834
a totally life-changing
opportunity,

22:30.834 --> 22:32.625
and so I had to follow it
through all the way.

22:32.625 --> 22:34.917
Yeah, so you left.

22:34.917 --> 22:37.917
- Yeah, but I'm here now.
- And I was sort of relieved.

22:40.917 --> 22:43.417
What?

22:43.417 --> 22:46.708
I mean, I didn't realize it
till after you were gone,
but, yeah.

22:48.625 --> 22:51.583
Why would you feel
that way?

22:53.291 --> 22:55.750
Did you think
it was working between us?

22:56.542 --> 22:58.417
I mean,
not all the time,

22:58.417 --> 23:02.500
but I really thought
the things that weren't
working, we could fix them.

23:02.500 --> 23:04.458
We tried this
all different kinds of ways.

23:04.458 --> 23:07.500
I don't know
any other ways.

23:07.500 --> 23:09.625
Do you?

23:11.291 --> 23:12.500
But it did work
for a while, right?

23:12.500 --> 23:16.125
Yeah, yeah, it worked like
a fuckin' charm, sometimes.

23:20.625 --> 23:23.834
What we had was... real,

23:23.834 --> 23:28.708
and it was beautiful
and intense and weird
and terrifying,

23:28.708 --> 23:32.125
and there was a time

23:32.125 --> 23:35.625
I couldn't imagine myself
with anyone else.

23:35.625 --> 23:37.667
Ever.

23:39.333 --> 23:43.333
( voice breaking )
But you don't feel
that way anymore.

23:43.333 --> 23:45.291
No.

23:48.166 --> 23:50.959
I'm so sorry.

23:50.959 --> 23:53.500
I know it seems fast
and really fuckin' weird,

23:53.500 --> 23:55.458
but it's what happened.

23:55.458 --> 23:57.875
( sniffles )

23:57.875 --> 24:01.333
I didn't plan on it,
but it's what happened.

24:01.333 --> 24:03.834
And I need to see
where it's gonna go.

24:08.208 --> 24:10.208
Do you love her?

24:18.166 --> 24:20.583
I don't know yet.

24:25.250 --> 24:27.000
Okay.

24:28.375 --> 24:29.792
I think it makes
the most sense

24:29.792 --> 24:31.458
for you to stay here,
so I'm gonna move out.

24:31.458 --> 24:33.708
Just give me
a couple days.

24:33.708 --> 24:35.792
Just change that
every 12 hours.

24:35.792 --> 24:37.834
You want me
to help you with this?

24:37.834 --> 24:40.000
I got it.
I got it, thanks.

24:44.417 --> 24:46.375
Okay.

24:54.000 --> 24:56.542
Thanks for
stopping by, kid.

24:58.875 --> 25:01.708
Thank you
for stopping by.

25:04.083 --> 25:07.208
But maybe don't
call me "kid" anymore.

25:07.208 --> 25:09.375
Okay, sure.

